@baseUrl = http://localhost:5067
@TeamMemberId = 1

# Swagger UI — open in browser: http://localhost:5067/swagger


### ─── JOBS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create Job
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: {{TeamMemberId}}

{
  "title": "Backend Developer",
  "description": "Build and maintain our ASP.NET Core APIs.",
  "location": "Remote",
  "status": 0
}

###

### List Jobs (all)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/jobs?page=1&pageSize=20
Accept: application/json

###

### List Jobs (open only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/jobs?status=open&page=1&pageSize=20
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Job By Id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/jobs/1
Accept: application/json

###


### ─── APPLICATIONS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create Application (public — no header needed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/jobs/1/applications
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "candidateName": "Jamie Doe",
  "candidateEmail": "jamie@example.com",
  "coverLetter": "I am excited to apply for this role."
}

###

### List Applications for Job
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/jobs/1/applications
Accept: application/json

###

### List Applications filtered by stage
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/jobs/1/applications?stage=screening
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Full Application Profile (cached in Redis 60s)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1
Accept: application/json

###


### ─── STAGE TRANSITIONS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Move to Screening
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/stage
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: {{TeamMemberId}}

{
  "toStage": 1,
  "reason": "Strong resume — moving to phone screen."
}

###

### Move to Interview
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/stage
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: {{TeamMemberId}}

{
  "toStage": 2,
  "reason": "Phone screen passed."
}

###

### Move to Offer
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/stage
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: {{TeamMemberId}}

{
  "toStage": 3,
  "reason": "Excellent panel interview."
}

###

### Move to Hired
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/stage
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: {{TeamMemberId}}

{
  "toStage": 4,
  "reason": "Offer accepted."
}

###

### Move to Rejected (valid from any non-terminal stage)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/stage
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: {{TeamMemberId}}

{
  "toStage": 5,
  "reason": "Position filled by another candidate."
}

###

### Invalid Transition — expect 400
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/stage
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: {{TeamMemberId}}

{
  "toStage": 4
}

###


### ─── NOTES ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Add a General Note
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/notes
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: {{TeamMemberId}}

{
  "type": 0,
  "description": "Strong initial impression — clear communicator."
}

###

### Add a Screening Note
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/notes
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: 2

{
  "type": 1,
  "description": "Phone screen confirmed technical fundamentals are solid."
}

###

### Add a Red Flag Note
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/notes
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: 3

{
  "type": 4,
  "description": "Candidate was unresponsive for 2 weeks mid-process."
}

###

### List Notes (newest first, author names resolved)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/notes
Accept: application/json

###


### ─── SCORES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Set Culture-Fit Score
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/scores/culture-fit
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: {{TeamMemberId}}

{
  "score": 4,
  "comment": "Aligned well with the team's values and communication style."
}

###

### Set Interview Score
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/scores/interview
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: 2

{
  "score": 5,
  "comment": "Excellent systems design and clear problem-solving approach."
}

###

### Set Assessment Score
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/scores/assessment
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: 2

{
  "score": 3,
  "comment": "Take-home was functional but lacked tests."
}

###

### Overwrite Assessment Score (PUT semantics — second write wins)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/applications/1/scores/assessment
Content-Type: application/json
X-Team-Member-Id: 3

{
  "score": 4,
  "comment": "Re-reviewed after candidate submitted improvements."
}

###


### ─── REFERENCE ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Seeded team members:
#   ID 1 = Alex Johnson  (Recruiter)
#   ID 2 = Sam Patel     (HiringManager)
#   ID 3 = Jordan Lee    (Recruiter)
#
# Stage enum values:
#   0 = Applied   1 = Screening   2 = Interview
#   3 = Offer     4 = Hired       5 = Rejected
#
# Note type enum values:
#   0 = General   1 = Screening   2 = Interview
#   3 = ReferenceCheck   4 = RedFlag
